            {
              "id": "CVE-2025-7709",
              "name": "OsPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2025-7709"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://scout.docker.com/v/CVE-2025-7709?s=debian&n=sqlite3&ns=debian&t=deb&osn=debian&osv=13&vr=%3C3.46.1-7%2Bdeb13u1",
              "help": {
                "text": "An integer overflow exists in the  FTS5 https://sqlite.org/fts5.html  extension. It occurs when the size of an array of tombstone pointers is calculated and truncated into a 32-bit integer. A pointer to partially controlled data can then be written out of bounds.\n\n---\n- sqlite3 3.46.1-8 (bug https://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=1114609)\n[trixie] - sqlite3 3.46.1-7+deb13u1\n[bookworm] - sqlite3 <no-dsa> (Minor issue)\n[bullseye] - sqlite3 <not-affected> (The vulnerable code was introduced later)\nhttps://github.com/google/security-research/security/advisories/GHSA-v2c8-vqqp-hv3g\nFixed by: https://sqlite.org/src/info/63595b74956a9391\nFixed by: https://github.com/sqlite/sqlite/commit/192d0ff8ccf0bf55776a5930cdc64e25f87299d6\n",
                "markdown": "> An integer overflow exists in the  FTS5 https://sqlite.org/fts5.html  extension. It occurs when the size of an array of tombstone pointers is calculated and truncated into a 32-bit integer. A pointer to partially controlled data can then be written out of bounds.\n\n---\n- sqlite3 3.46.1-8 (bug https://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=1114609)\n[trixie] - sqlite3 3.46.1-7+deb13u1\n[bookworm] - sqlite3 <no-dsa> (Minor issue)\n[bullseye] - sqlite3 <not-affected> (The vulnerable code was introduced later)\nhttps://github.com/google/security-research/security/advisories/GHSA-v2c8-vqqp-hv3g\nFixed by: https://sqlite.org/src/info/63595b74956a9391\nFixed by: https://github.com/sqlite/sqlite/commit/192d0ff8ccf0bf55776a5930cdc64e25f87299d6\n\n|                                                                                               |\n|Package         pkg:deb/debian/sqlite3@3.46.1-7?os_distro=trixie&os_name=debian&os_version=13  |\n|Affected range  <3.46.1-7+deb13u1                                                              |\n|Fixed version   3.46.1-7+deb13u1                                                               |\n"
              },
